==English==

===Noun===
'''cramp'''  (''plural'' '''[[cramps]]''')
#A [[painful]] [[contraction]] of a [[muscle]] which cannot be [[control]]led.
#A [[clamp]] for [[carpentry]] or [[masonry]].

====Translations====
{{top}}
*French: [[crampe]] ''f''
*German: [[Krampf]] ''m'' (1), [[Klammer]] ''f'' (2)
*Ido: [[krampo]]
{{mid}}
{{bottom}}

===Verb===
'''to cramp'''  ('''cramps''', '''cramped''', '''cramping''')
#''(intransitive)'' (of a muscle) to [[contract]] [[painful]]ly and [[uncontrollable|uncontrollably]]
<!--I'm not quite sure but isn't the next definition a definition of "to cramp someone's style" rather than "to cramp" in general?-->
#''(transitive)'' to prohibit movement or expression
#:''You're '''cramping''' my style.''
#''(transitive)'' to restrain to a specific physical position.
#:''You're going to need to '''cramp''' the wheels on this hill.''

